cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.DM, cs.GT. 

The paper deals with a computational geometry problem (Point Line Cover) and uses techniques from data structures, complexity theory, and graph theory. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses lower bounds and algorithms, which are relevant to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the paper uses order types, which are a concept from combinatorial geometry, making cs.GT (Discrete Geometry and Topology) a possible sub-category as well.
